content:
Hi all, not sure if this is the right place to ask questions about the Beacon Chain spec. I was looking at the definition of `is_slashable_validator`:
```
def is_slashable_validator(validator: Validator, epoch: Epoch) -> bool:
    return (not validator.slashed) and (validator.activation_epoch <= epoch < validator.withdrawable_epoch)
```
So it seems that validators are slashable even after they have exited. I was wondering if this is actually currently possible, since as far as I know validators cannot attest/propose anymore after exiting, so how would they get slashed?
